Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

reviewerName: DICK YORK IS THE BETTER DICK "Sterculeus Erectus"
reviewText: The 5th Season oif MR ED pulled out all the special effects stops you could possibly do with a horse...very funny season. Short on intelligent plots but still very funny. This was the last good season and the last with neighbor Colonel kirkwoood. After this season the show brought in Carol's father but the show was out of ideas and was cancelled 13 episodes into the 6th season. Show was limited by being primarily for children by this time and by the limits of censorship in 1965 era. but get season 5 many funny episodes. I guess they will only release 13 episodes to complete the series on DVD ..and I hope at half the price since it is half a season. Pl FYI All seasons are uncut escept 8 prints from season one (thankfully of mainly unfunny episodes..why they used edited prints for those 8 episodes seems to have been a mistake they had the uncut films .but were unaware the prints they used were edited until AFTER they released the first season..oh well..and a Horse is a horse......I would love to see a POLITICAL remake of this show with the kind of raunchy and politcal comments from ED you could not get away with in 1965...EXAMPLE... Wilbur in front of neighbors "MY friends I want to welcome all of you here tonight" ED chimes in the background " And  welcome All of you illegal border crossers  making my dinner."  just an idea lol

reviewText: Why doesn't the studio or distributor of Seasons 4 & 5 of Mister Ed just let Amazon sell these sets? If they would like to see the sales go UP on them, they would benefit from doing so, which should drop the price closer to the first 3 seasons... I'd buy them right now if they did and I'm sure a lot of others would too. I'm sure I'm not the only one who's held out on this and I have no intentions on buying unless Amazon does the selling. Same goes for the last 2 released seasons of Ironside.

Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

reviewText: I love this show!  I did not realize as a kid how adult the humor was since I was just a kid.  I always thought it was just a kid show!  Now I appreciate the adult themes and humor as an adult with very fine actors to pull it off!  Thank you, Alan Young &  Connie HInes.  Thank you, Larry Keating & Edna Skinner.  And of course, thank you, Bamboo Harvester as Mr. Ed :) and his later neighbors Leon Ames & Florence MacMichael. :)
summary: A horse is a horse of course of course & Alan Young is Par Excelleance!!!
Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

reviewText: This is the penultimate season to Mister Ed.I have certainly enjoyed all five seasons and await the sixth and final season.The show is very funny considering the premise that it is about a horse that talks.Sounds silly.But it isn't.All the family can enjoy it By now, Larry Keating who played the neighbor next door, had passed on and been replaced.His character of Addison was brilliant and was in some respects the highlight of the show.But this series is still great tv and a joy to watch.You'll believe a horse can talk.

Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

reviewText: Ordered all 5 seasons, and it has made me so happy! The special effects for the times that these shows were produced is amazing! The writing is so clever, and the acting is suberb, especially Edna Skinner . Mr. Ed's delivery of lines is right on the mark. I wish that Season 6 would come out! With TV so trashy and lousy these days it would be so worth the price to get it!
summary: I am hooked on this show!
Title: Mister Ed: Season 5

reviewText: The show is as great now as it was when first aired. I only wish that there were still shows like this produced now. Watching all the seasons again brings back great memories from childhood and is also creating the same with new additions to the family. Also, the buyer that it was purchased from sent it in a timely manner and in the condition promised.
